        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-16T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-16T23:00:00-05:00" n="530" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/3–1749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-17T12:00:00+08:00">March 17, 1949—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 17—1:26 a.
                        m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>588. ReEmbtel 487, February 28, and Deptel 297, March 4. In light of Ho
                    Ying-chin’s appointment as Premier and forthcoming reorganization of Cabinet,
                    Acting President requests that US Government resume shipment of military
                    materiel procured by Chinese Government. Acting President hopes it will be
                    possible to recommence deliveries to Chinese ports, including Taiwan, soon as
                    possible.</p>
                <p>I recommend Department comply with request of Acting President.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 588, repeated Canton 166.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
